medical_history.chief_complaint: Congenital fibrosis of the extraocular muscles (CFEOM), facial weakness, intellectual and social disabilities, and anosmia.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The symptoms began at birth with nonprogressive bilateral ptosis, paralytic strabismus, and facial weakness. The patient displayed developmental delay and learning disabilities. Pubertal onset was normal with menarche between age 12-13. Numbness and paresthesias in feet developed over time, and irregular menstrual cycles varied between 30 to 50 days. Electrophysiologic evidence revealed moderately severe sensorimotor polyneuropathy.
medical_history.past_medical_history: The patient has a history of Moebius syndrome. She underwent strabismus surgery and had three spontaneous pregnancies. She has a history of delayed motor development, learning disabilities, and emotional modulation difficulties.
